The '''golden-breasted fulvetta''' ('''''Lioparus chrysotis''''') is a species of [[songbird]] found in [[Bhutan]], [[China]], [[India]], [[Myanmar]], [[Nepal]], and [[Vietnam]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are temperate [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s.

